TO PLANCUS

AMED Rhodes, Apollo’s Delphi, Mitylene, Or Corinth's walls, two seas between, Thessalian Tempe, Thebes through Bacchus known, And Ephesus I let alone. In builded strains some only hymn thy town, Chaste Pallas ; and the olive crown Adoms their temples, cropped on every hand. For Juno's praise a goodly band Home-nursing Argos, rich Mycenae, name. . xMe neither stubbom Sparta’s fame Nor yet Larissa's teeming plain so moves As Anio’s rush, Tiburtine groveS, Those orchards, that the nimble runnels lave Beside Albunea's echoing cave. oft Notus whitens all the murky sky And rain descends not from on high. So in thy Tibur's deeper shade, or where The comps with blazing signals glare, Plancus, be wise; life’s woes and toils decline, Go, drown them all in mellow wine.
